'''CO-STAR''' is an iterative [[innovation management]] methodology originating from silicon valley.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wills|first1=Anamaria|title=CO-STAR – An innovation tool for creating compelling customer value|url=https://4creativentrepreneurs.wordpress.com/2013/03/25/co-star-an-innovation-tool-for-creating-compelling-customer-value/|accessdate=6 January 2017}}</ref> The acronym stands for ''customer, opportunity, solution, team, advantages'' and ''results''. It was introduced in a 2012 book by Laszlo Gyorffy and Lisa Friedman.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Gyorffy|first1=Laszlo|last2=Friedman|first2=Lisa|title=Creating Value with CO-STAR: An Innovation Tool for Perfecting and Pitching Your Brilliant Idea|date=31 August 2012|publisher=Enterprise Development Group, Inc|isbn=978-0985941901}}</ref>
The methodology is being used by several companies, for example by INNOArchitects, [[IdeaScale]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Timpany|first1=Greg|title=Use the COSTAR Model to Polish Ideas Into Innovations|url=http://researchaccess.com/2014/11/costar-model/|accessdate=6 January 2017}}</ref> or the [[Swiss Post]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Swiss Post INNOTOOLS|url=https://post.innotools.com/en/home|accessdate=6 January 2017}}</ref>
