'''FeeFighters''' is a comparison shopping website for credit card processing. The site was launched in 2009<ref>[http://feefighters.com/about About]</ref> and acquired by Groupon in April 2013. FeeFighters has been featured in [[The New York Times]], [[Entrepreneur (magazine)]], [[Inc. (magazine)]] and [[TechCrunch]], with [[BusinessWeek]] profiling it as "One of America's Most Promising Startups."<ref name="nytimes">Mandelbaum, Robb. [http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/10/17/in-battle-with-merchants-banks-still-hope-to-overturn-durbin-amendment/ In Battling Merchants, Banks Still Hope to Overturn Durbin Rules]. "New York Times". October 18, 2011</ref><ref name="entrepreneur">Chapman, Glenn. [http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/219681 How to Cut Transaction Costs on Customer Purchases]. ''Entrepreneur''. May 20, 2011.</ref><ref name="inc">Greenstein, Howard. [http://www.inc.com/howard-greenstein/fight-credit-card-processing-fees.html Fight Credit Card Processing Fees]. ''Inc.''. May 25, 2011.</ref><ref name="BusinessWeek">Tozzi, John. [http://images.businessweek.com/slideshows/20110211/america-s-most-promising-startups/slides/8 America's Most Promising Startups]. ''BusinessWeek''. Feb. 4, 2011</ref><ref name="CreditCardFlyers">Parrish, Leni. [http://www.creditcardflyers.com/credit-card-news/2012/credit-card-comparison-service-feefighters-bought-by-groupon-3372.php Credit Card Comparison Service FeeFighters Bought By Groupon]. ''CreditCardFlyers''. March. 27, 2012</ref>

