The '''[[intermodulation]] intercept point''' is a measure of an electrical device's [[linearity]]. When driven by two [[sinusoidal wave]]forms, it is the theoretical power level at which the power of the desired tone and the nth-order (where n is odd) intermodulation product intersect.

